(131, 'Control Statements', 'How many times the while loop will get executed if a short int is 2 byte wide?', '#include&lt;stdio.h&gt;\nint main()\n{\n    int j=1;\n    while(j &lt;= 255)\n    {\n        printf(&quot;%c %d\\n&quot;, j, j);\n        j++;\n    }\n    return 0;\n}', 'Infinite time', '255 times', '256 times', '254 times', 2, 'The while(j &lt;= 255) loop will get executed 255 times. The size short int(2 byte wide) does not affect the while() loop.'),
