(142, 'Control Statements', 'What will be the output of the given program?', '#include&lt;stdio.h&gt;\nvoid main()\n{\n	int a=11,b=5;\n	if(a=5) b++;\n	printf(&quot;%d %d&quot;, ++a, b++);\n}', 'a)	11  7', 'b)	12  8', 'c)	6  6', 'd)	6  7', 3, 'Here if condition evaluates to true as a non-zero value i.e 5 is assigned to a.\nSo the value of a = 5 and after increment value of b = 6.\nIn printf statement due to pre-increment of a value of a printed will be 6 and due to post-increment of b value of b printed will be 6 and not 7.'),
